outputs.description: National and local partners have increased capacity to provide systematic identification, case management and appropriate follow-upof child victims or children at risk.
Independent institutions, government and civil society have strengthened capacity to monitor child rights in line withinternational norms.
National capacity to apply child- friendly proceedings, alternatives to detention and diversion in line with international norms isenhanced.
Programme planning and monitoring: UNICEF staff and partners are provided with guidance, tools and resources to effectively planand monitor programmes.
Communications Advocacy & Partnerships: UNICEF staff and partners are provided tools, guidance and resources for effectiveadvocacy and partnerships on child rights issues with stakeholders
Cross-sectoral approaches: Strategies to address cross-cutting issues related to child rights are developed and applied.
National partners have enhanced capacity to extend access to preschool, basic and post-basic education to the most vulnerablechildren.
National partners have increased capacity to provide quality learning through life skills education.

Data and analytical evidence on child wellbeing, multidimensional poverty and vulnerability, disaggregated by sex, geographicalareas and disability status, are regularly available to inform policy and monitor progress towards the child-relevant SustainableDevelopment Goals.
